Methods.method_description: Creates a new, reusable property list decoder.

params.param_description: The type of the value to decode from the supplied property list.

Methods.method_description: Returns a value of the specified type by decoding a property list using the default property list format.
Methods.method_declar: func decode<T>(_ type: T.Type, from data: Data) throws -> T where T : Decodable

Methods.method_description: Returns a value of the specified type by decoding a property list using the supplied format.
Methods.method_declar: func decode<T>(_ type: T.Type, from data: Data, format: inout PropertyListSerialization.PropertyListFormat) throws -> T where T : Decodable

Vars.var_description: A dictionary you use to customize decoding by providing contextual information.
